eNCA's Nobesuthu Hejena has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A Human Sciences Research Council photographic exhibition, depicting the aftermath of the 2015 Fees Must Fall protests, aims to create awareness about mental health. It also wants to destigmatize mental illness and create spaces for students to speak freely about their experiences. READ: Violence of Fees Must Fall protests has damaged cause: 2016 Matric class A total of 34 images are on display at the University of Cape Town. The research council says conversations should not focus on the ineffectiveness of the protests but rather on how violent protests should be avoided at all institutions of learning due to the mental damage they cause.